Str dex agi and sta are not wasted on casters at all.  I have my dex and agi BOTH over 100 and keep them there because the mobs miss more, AGI keeps my AC higher, and stanima gives me more hitpoints, not a lot more, but hey every little bit counts to a chatner.  My 86 str, buffed easily into the 100's has saved my butt several times when I have had to melee off the last bit of a mob, or am so loaded down with stuff that it keeps my agi from falling (hence lowering my AC).  My STA I try to keep as close to 90 as possible and even would like that to reach 100 110.  The idea that only melees NEED these stats is pretty narrow-minded.  Heck I propably get hit a lot more often then any hybred in my groups due to the nature of the class I play, YET my gear is so deficient in the areas that could help to keep me alive (AC/Hit Points, etc..) Chanters don't die becuase they run out of mana, they die becuase they run out of hit points...OH BTW I see 7 chanter stats.. AC/Mana/HPS/CHR/INT/STA/AGI and that is the order in which I would rank a cloak.  Name one other cloak out there (besides the loam one) that has a chr bonus??  I do not know of any and would love to see another. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ucelarastarshine.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celara Starshine</A> at: 5/16/01 10:04:21 am<br></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousgeneral.showMessage?topicID=2491.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousgeneral.showMessage?topicID=2476.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub12.ezboard.com/ftorvonnilousgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=2414.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http